WEBVTT

00:01.610 --> 00:02.736
Micah:
Previously on
"Queen Sugar"...

00:02.780 --> 00:04.509
Me_and Mama
getting married.

00:04.560 --> 00:07.120
-So, you'll be
together forever?
-Forever.

00:07.180 --> 00:09.216
Robert:
Zika, it's a hurricane
by another name.

00:09.270 --> 00:11.613
And believe me, Nova,
you connected the dots.

00:11.660 --> 00:13.218
Charley:
Hello, Mother.

00:13.270 --> 00:16.569
I'm the first black woman
to own a mill in the state.

00:16.620 --> 00:18.315
Will you be satisfied
with this?

00:18.360 --> 00:20.351
You know, your hair
it's falling out a little.

00:20.410 --> 00:23.015
You might need to get this
checked out, girl.

00:23.060 --> 00:24.925
About that night,
we have to tell your mother.

00:24.980 --> 00:26.493
She doesn't wanna
hear about it.

00:26.540 --> 00:28.679
- What's eating you?
- Something happened to Micah.

00:30.760 --> 00:32.284
[ music playing ]

00:32.330 --> 00:33.843
Good to see you.

00:35.680 --> 00:37.466
All right.
Thank you.

00:38.950 --> 00:40.850
[ clears throat ]

00:47.610 --> 00:49.089
Why you looking at me
like that?

00:49.130 --> 00:52.258
Ernest giving you this farm
was the best thing

00:52.310 --> 00:53.868
that could have
happened to you.

00:53.920 --> 00:55.740
- Look what it's done.
- Man, watch out, Aunt Vi.

00:57.750 --> 00:59.741
I ain't gonna
mess this up, Aunt Vi.

00:59.790 --> 01:01.963
Well, speaking about things
you ain't gonna mess up.

01:04.490 --> 01:07.277
You wanna make sure
you stay on track wrth Darla.

01:07.320 --> 01:10.494
This is something
they started at my church.

01:10.540 --> 01:14.715
For the young folk
getting married and divorced
like it isn't sacred no more.

01:14.770 --> 01:17.933
_Ain't no shame
In getting adVIce.

01:17.990 --> 01:21.209
Even those that think
they got it all figured out
learn something.

01:21.250 --> 01:24.856
And it's free,
so don't give me
nothing about that.

01:27.520 --> 01:29.988
[ sighs ]

01:30.040 --> 01:31.473
You look like
you're feeling better.

01:31.520 --> 01:33.124
Iam.

01:33.180 --> 01:36.217
-[laughs]
- About to get
outta here, Aunt Vi.

01:44.270 --> 01:45.828
I love you, Aunt Vi.

01:46.970 --> 01:47.925
I'll see ya.

01:50.580 --> 01:53.538
- Hi. Can I help you?
- Good morning.

01:53.590 --> 01:57.708
You know
where I might find
Miss Bordelon?

01:57.760 --> 01:59.318
May I ask why?

01:59.380 --> 02:01.940
Well, a manager
at Delta Diner told me

02:01.990 --> 02:06.336
that Miss Bordelon
made the best pie
I've ever tasted.

02:06.380 --> 02:09.167
- What kind of pie?
- Cherry.

02:09.210 --> 02:11.519
Tart, sweet,

02:11.560 --> 02:13.733
flaky crust to die for.

02:13.780 --> 02:17.386
Yeah, well,
if you pass on
from my pies,

02:17.440 --> 02:19.169
that's gonna hurt
my business.

02:19.220 --> 02:20.824
So, you're Miss Bordelon?

02:20.870 --> 02:23.395
It's an honor
to meet you.

02:23.440 --> 02:26.318
Kind of you
to come this way,
pay a compliment.

02:26.360 --> 02:29.090
Oh, well,
that's not the only reason
for my business.

02:29.140 --> 02:31.700
I'm Jarrett Rawlings
of Rawlings Supermarkets.

02:31.760 --> 02:33.489
We got stores
in three parishes--

02:33.540 --> 02:36.407
And I do plenty of shopping
at the one in St. Jo's.

02:36.460 --> 02:38.758
Y'all's
double coupon Thursday--

02:38.810 --> 02:40.539
best thing going.

02:40.590 --> 02:42.933
Well, thank you.
That was my idea.

02:42.980 --> 02:44.242
Good one.

02:44.290 --> 02:46.758
I hope you like my--

02:46.810 --> 02:48.687
my latest brainstorm.

02:53.650 --> 02:57.290
We'd like you to provide us
with 350 pies a week

02:57.350 --> 02:59.773
to sell exclusively
in our stores.

03:02.130 --> 03:05.213
All the terms
are laid out there.

03:05.270 --> 03:07.488
I think you'll find everything
is more than adequate.

03:15.800 --> 03:18.496
[ theme music playing ]

03:18.540 --> 03:22.749
Dreams never die,
take flight,
as the world turns

03:22.810 --> 03:26.155
Dreams never die,
take flight,
as the world turns

03:26.200 --> 03:28.634
Keep the colors
in the lines, take flight

03:30.640 --> 03:32.198
Dreams never die

03:37.910 --> 03:41.994
Keep the colors
in the lines

03:42.040 --> 03:44.736
Keep the colors
in the lines, take flight.

03:49.220 --> 03:52.223
Why is blood
flowing through this body?

03:52.270 --> 03:54.579
Why is air in my lung?

03:57.360 --> 03:59.578
Where we goin' now?

03:59.630 --> 04:02.053
Why did I get
to place my feet here?

04:02.110 --> 04:06.012
Thy kingdom come,
Thy kingdom come

04:06.070 --> 04:11.246
Oh, I got a song to sing

04:11.290 --> 04:14.157
And it's a song
about hope for you

04:14.210 --> 04:16.678
It's a song about faith

04:16.730 --> 04:21.554
I see all
that you are going through

04:21.600 --> 04:24.421
And it's gonna be all right

04:24.480 --> 04:27.256
- Thanks, Pop.
- ...gonna be all right

04:27.310 --> 04:29.778
It's gonna be all right

04:29.830 --> 04:32.219
It's gonna be all right

04:32.270 --> 04:35.046
Everything's
gonna be all right

04:35.100 --> 04:37.660
It's gonna be
all right

04:37.710 --> 04:40.793
It's gonna be all right

04:40.840 --> 04:42.228
It's gonna be...

04:42.280 --> 04:44.089
[sighs]
Oh...

04:45.190 --> 04:46.532
Hi.

04:46.590 --> 04:49.491
- Mm.
- Oh! Whew.

04:51.760 --> 04:52.931
Huh?

05:01.640 --> 05:05.337
You're still thinking
about your father's will,
aren't you?

05:05.390 --> 05:08.860
Charlotte, you can't
dwell on this forever.

05:19.140 --> 05:21.358
I just wanna know
why Daddy did it.

05:23.620 --> 05:26.441
Why he didn't
discuss it with me.

05:26.500 --> 05:30.140
The truth is, your daddy
was a man who changed his mind.

05:32.540 --> 05:36.192
But what you have now,
it's far greater
than that land.

05:36.240 --> 05:38.413
The mill.

05:38.460 --> 05:41.634
'Cause it's yours.
It is yours alone.

05:41.680 --> 05:43.591
I'm not sure
how much good
that is anymore

05:43.640 --> 05:47.519
since a huge part
of my business plan
was tied to the farm.

05:47.560 --> 05:50.074
Now, that is something
that I can help you with

05:50.130 --> 05:52.030
if you just give me
a few hours.

05:54.780 --> 05:55.917
Okay.

06:00.750 --> 06:02.172
Thank you.

06:04.050 --> 06:06.314
Charley, you're gonna
get through this.

06:17.630 --> 06:18.938
Let me help.

06:18.980 --> 06:21.767
Huh. I told you,
no physical labor.

06:21.810 --> 06:25.940
You're just here
to check in the volunteers
as they arrive.

06:25.990 --> 06:29.289
Please. I'm just glad
I could still use my body

06:29.340 --> 06:31.513
for more than
just feeding the twins.

06:31.560 --> 06:35.348
- How are they?
- Growing like weeds,
and too young to resent me

06:35.390 --> 06:38.086
for taking a few hours
to help you, sister soldier.

06:38.130 --> 06:39.995
And I can't
thank you enough.

06:40.050 --> 06:41.779
Hello.

06:41.830 --> 06:46.574
Robert,
meet my oldest friend
from Tulane-- Sierra.

06:46.620 --> 06:50.659
Oh, this is the friendship
that began with the fight

06:50.710 --> 06:52.052
about whether or not
Black History Month

06:52.100 --> 06:54.967
is a form _
of self-segregation.

06:55.020 --> 06:56.715
- Nova: Mm-hmm.
- She won that fight,
by the way.

06:56.760 --> 06:59.228
Uh-huh.
Of course she did.

06:59.280 --> 07:00.679
[ women chuckle ]

07:00.720 --> 07:05.191
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you, too.

07:05.250 --> 07:08.469
I'm surprised at how quickly
you pulled all this together.

07:08.510 --> 07:11.502
- Ooh!
- Go on.

07:11.560 --> 07:14.120
- No, I know
you wanna say it.
- Are you talking to me?

07:14.170 --> 07:16.161
Yeah, some kind
of "I told you so."

07:16.210 --> 07:19.031
Since Timothy North's
donation is the reason
we could do this so fast.

07:19.090 --> 07:21.775
There's nothing wrong
with giving a bit of credit
where credit is due.

07:21.830 --> 07:23.604
You can give him
all the credit you want;

07:23.660 --> 07:24.820
he still a horse's ass.

07:24.870 --> 07:27.953
[ Sierra and Robert
laughing ]

07:28.010 --> 07:30.228
Yes, he is.
See?

07:30.270 --> 07:32.056
Always wins.

07:32.100 --> 07:34.660
- What a pleasure.
- A pleasure.

07:40.460 --> 07:41.791
Mmm...

07:41.850 --> 07:43.408
Last I heard,
you were done dating.

07:43.460 --> 07:45.360
Now you with
a damn unicorn.

07:45.420 --> 07:46.489
We ain't like that.

07:46.550 --> 07:49.189
Really?
The way he looks at you?

07:49.250 --> 07:51.855
- How is it, then?
- We have a lot of respect
for each other's work.

07:51.900 --> 07:53.549
Uh-uh, that's not
what I asked.

07:53.600 --> 07:56.467
How... is... it?

07:58.260 --> 08:00.125
- Well...
- Ooh!

08:00.170 --> 08:02.035
That's what I thought!

08:03.520 --> 08:05.476
Girl, look, I just want
the best for you,

08:05.520 --> 08:07.909
so give this man a chance
to be like that.

08:07.960 --> 08:09.871
'Cause if you don't,
I'm gonna scoop him up
for myself.

08:09.920 --> 08:11.911
You know what?
Come on, gIrl.
We got work to do.

08:11.960 --> 08:13.439
And don't you lift
nothing.

08:13.490 --> 08:15.617
Matter of fact,
stack them bottles
one by one.

08:15.660 --> 08:17.139
- I'm watching you.
- Mm-hmm.

08:17.190 --> 08:18.532
- One by one.
- Miss Bossy. Yes, ma'am.

08:18.580 --> 08:20.093
[ both laugh ]

08:27.150 --> 08:29.061
[ music playing ]

08:31.770 --> 08:34.671
I was tempted
from the beginning

08:34.730 --> 08:37.767
Swallowing
these second guesses

08:37.820 --> 08:40.721
'Cause I had you
in my mind

08:40.780 --> 08:43.817
Baby

08:43.870 --> 08:46.828
Following your thirst
and sweat

08:46.870 --> 08:49.600
On a whim
when first we met

08:49.650 --> 08:53.131
I just had
to rewind it

08:55.790 --> 08:58.702
Got me spellbound
with that face

08:58.750 --> 09:01.742
And the way
you move that waist

09:01.800 --> 09:05.270
Thinking
"Can I get a taste?"

09:05.320 --> 09:08.539
Mmm...

09:08.590 --> 09:09.534
Wow.

09:11.590 --> 09:13.410
That dress looks
beautiful on you.

09:13.460 --> 09:14.711
What do you think?

09:14.770 --> 09:17.637
_ _ I think that _
It IS way too expenSIve.

09:19.730 --> 09:21.812
Do you really like it?

09:21.860 --> 09:23.771
You can be honest.

09:23.820 --> 09:26.596
Darla, honesty
is in my blood.

09:26.650 --> 09:31.212
My mother is the queen
of brutal honesty.

09:32.870 --> 09:34.303
[ sighs ]

09:34.350 --> 09:36.523
I was with her when I went
wedding dress shopping.

09:36.570 --> 09:39.221
[ chuckles ]
I had fallen in love

09:39.270 --> 09:41.261
with the first dress
that I ever tried on.

09:41.310 --> 09:43.050
People say
that never happens.

09:44.670 --> 09:47.889
But my mother,
she hated it.

09:50.670 --> 09:54.231
She said that it made me
look pregnant...

09:55.850 --> 09:58.193
which I was.

09:58.240 --> 09:59.673
But...

10:02.900 --> 10:04.458
Yeah.

10:06.820 --> 10:11.291
My mother knew that,
but refused to accept it.

10:11.340 --> 10:14.161
She didn't
want her friends

10:14.220 --> 10:17.383
believing that her daughter
was having a shotgun wedding.

10:20.660 --> 10:23.049
And I wasn't.

10:23.100 --> 10:28.220
I mean, Davis and I,
we loved each other.

10:28.270 --> 10:32.445
But my mother
was disappointed,

10:32.500 --> 10:34.445
to say the least.

10:35.760 --> 10:38.843
And she did not
try to hide it.

10:38.890 --> 10:40.938
Not from me.

10:44.250 --> 10:45.638
The point is...

10:48.290 --> 10:50.554
[ chuckles ]
if I didn't think
that dress looked

10:50.600 --> 10:53.330
anything short
of beautiful on you,
you would know.

10:58.440 --> 11:01.341
- Oh, no, wait, did--
did I say something?
- [ sobs, sniffles ]

11:01.390 --> 11:04.348
I'm sorry,
it's, um--

11:04.400 --> 11:09.099
it's just my family
doesn't even care_that
I'm getting married.

11:09.140 --> 11:13.964
I called them
to tell them...

11:15.450 --> 11:17.406
I haven't heard back.

11:17.450 --> 11:20.408
Well, how long has it been
since you've talked?

11:20.460 --> 11:22.189
Years.

11:24.030 --> 11:26.498
Well, that must have
taken a lot.

11:26.550 --> 11:28.723
Yes.

11:28.770 --> 11:30.726
My mom actually sounds
a lot like yours.

11:30.770 --> 11:33.637
-[sobs]
-Mmm.

11:35.650 --> 11:37.379
I always just
wanted to please her.

11:39.480 --> 11:43.439
I think...
[ sighs ]

11:43.480 --> 11:45.914
when I called her...

11:48.490 --> 11:50.435
a piece of me was
still doing that.

11:51.790 --> 11:53.223
Probably
most of me.

11:54.580 --> 11:56.889
I just wanted her
to see...

11:59.320 --> 12:00.878
how far I'd come.

12:04.020 --> 12:07.103
So she wouldn't
feel like

12:07.160 --> 12:09.799
she's embarrassed
of her daughter.

12:12.730 --> 12:14.630
Just proud.

12:16.380 --> 12:19.031
Well,

12:19.080 --> 12:20.900
I don't know why
they haven't called back.

12:20.950 --> 12:24.124
But I know this:

12:24.170 --> 12:26.695
You have a family--

12:26.740 --> 12:31.473
Ralph Angel and Blue--
and another one_that
you're about to jom.

12:31.530 --> 12:38.220
So even if you never
hear from them again,

12:38.270 --> 12:42.445
you are still surrounded
by people who love you.

12:44.580 --> 12:45.751
Thank you.

12:54.510 --> 12:58.628
Admit it,
you'd rather be here

12:58.690 --> 13:00.555
than editing white papers
with your colleagues

13:00.600 --> 13:02.727
in some ivory tower
right now.

13:02.780 --> 13:05.738
Technically, my colleagues are
actually on the golf course
right now,

13:05.780 --> 13:09.773
but this definitely leads
to a stronger sense
of accomplishment.

13:09.830 --> 13:11.388
[ grunts ]

13:13.740 --> 13:15.742
Damn, Aunt Nova!
Look at those guns.

13:15.790 --> 13:18.748
Micah, I didn't know
you were coming.

13:18.790 --> 13:20.314
Neither did I.

13:20.360 --> 13:21.873
It was Keke's idea.

13:21.930 --> 13:23.181
- Hi.
- Hey.

13:23.230 --> 13:24.879
Oh, you two
have never met.

13:24.930 --> 13:27.660
Okay, Aunt Nova,
this is my girl, Keke.

13:27.710 --> 13:29.530
- Keke, Aunt Nova.
- Hi.

13:29.590 --> 13:31.717
I've heard so much
about you from Micah's mom.

13:31.760 --> 13:34.194
And I love your writing
and everything you do
for the community,

13:34.240 --> 13:36.379
and just--
you're an inspiration.

13:36.420 --> 13:39.287
Hey, I didn't know
you were a super fan.

13:39.340 --> 13:40.853
And this is
Dr. Dubois.

13:40.900 --> 13:43.073
Just Robert.
Pleasure to meet you.

13:43.120 --> 13:45.111
- Good to see you, young man.
- You, too, man.

13:45.170 --> 13:48.128
Well, I think I see
the news crews from
Channel 6 over there.

13:48.170 --> 13:49.728
We should probably
go talk to them.

13:49.780 --> 13:51.736
Thank you both so much
for helping us out today.

13:51.780 --> 13:54.476
- Of course, of course.
- Good to see you.

13:54.520 --> 13:56.215
- Nice to meet you.
- [ mouths ] Bye.

13:57.570 --> 13:59.299
I know. [ chuckles ]

13:59.360 --> 14:00.782
Cool.

14:04.880 --> 14:06.404
Hey, man,
I'm Micah.

14:06.450 --> 14:07.747
Leon.

14:09.230 --> 14:12.711
- [ man sighs ]
- [ metal thudding ]

14:28.950 --> 14:30.030
Hey.

14:31.300 --> 14:33.120
I'm ready.

14:34.350 --> 14:36.602
All right.

14:36.650 --> 14:41.269
- [ sighs ]
- So, I was thinking...

14:41.310 --> 14:43.437
- You was thinking.
- I was thinking

14:43.490 --> 14:46.789
we should get
a porch swing
for the house

14:46.840 --> 14:49.354
so we can look up
at the stars at night.

14:49.410 --> 14:50.570
Blue would love that.

14:50.620 --> 14:52.702
[ chuckles ]

14:52.760 --> 14:56.662
Ain't even moved in yet,
and she already takin' over.

14:56.720 --> 14:58.972
No, I just--
I think it'd be nice

14:59.020 --> 15:00.544
to switch things up
a little bit

15:00.590 --> 15:02.638
so it feels different,

15:02.680 --> 15:04.807
like a clean slate.

15:06.730 --> 15:09.722
As long as
I got you and Blue
under the same roof,

15:09.770 --> 15:11.852
I'm good.

15:11.910 --> 15:15.380
You should make it your own.
It's your home too, now.

15:19.350 --> 15:21.568
- My house too, now.
- [ chuckles ]

15:21.610 --> 15:23.259
[ chuckles ]

15:34.710 --> 15:36.928
- [ tailgate closes ]
- [ clears throat]

15:36.970 --> 15:39.109
What is this?

15:39.150 --> 15:41.198
Just Vi being Vi.

15:41.240 --> 15:43.458
Premarital counseling.

15:43.500 --> 15:44.808
I think it's
a good idea.

15:44.850 --> 15:47.193
Why? We good.

15:47.250 --> 15:49.980
We doing it on our own,
been doing it.

15:50.030 --> 15:53.682
No, I know,
but it's kind of
like doing your steps.

15:53.730 --> 15:57.075
I think it'd really help us
if things get hard, or...

15:57.130 --> 15:58.779
I ain't down with
no counseling, Darla.

15:58.820 --> 16:01.345
If I'm gonna get
advice from someone,

16:01.390 --> 16:03.517
it ain't gonna be some priest
who never been married.

16:03.570 --> 16:05.515
[ scoffs ]

16:05.570 --> 16:07.265
What's he gonna tell me
about being a husband?

16:07.310 --> 16:08.436
[ chuckles ]

16:21.280 --> 16:23.236
[ knocks ]

16:24.800 --> 16:26.415
Well, I...

16:31.680 --> 16:33.022
What are you
doing here?

16:34.810 --> 16:36.721
I'm helping Charley
with her business plan.

16:36.770 --> 16:38.556
I mean here
in St. Jo.

16:41.000 --> 16:42.991
We had an agreement.

16:43.040 --> 16:44.519
Yes, we did.

16:44.560 --> 16:46.733
But then my daughter
chose to move herself

16:46.780 --> 16:48.338
and my grandson here
full-time.

16:48.390 --> 16:51.132
- And that don't change nothing.
- Of course it does.

16:51.180 --> 16:52.738
You can't keep me
from seeing my family.

16:52.790 --> 16:55.133
I ain't worried
about your family.

16:55.180 --> 16:58.650
You can buy them
plane tickets to see you
on any continent.

16:58.710 --> 17:01.440
I'm worried
about mine.

17:01.490 --> 17:04.618
And I won't have you
upsetting Nova.

17:04.670 --> 17:06.626
Nova is
a grown woman.

17:06.670 --> 17:08.843
Who just lost her daddy
for the second time

17:08.890 --> 17:12.064
after you stole him
the first time.

17:12.110 --> 17:15.329
You coming around here
is just gonna stir
all that up,

17:15.380 --> 17:17.371
and that's wrong.

17:19.160 --> 17:21.549
I am sorry
about your brother,

17:21.600 --> 17:24.819
because I know how much
he meant to you.

17:40.840 --> 17:42.000
[ door slams ]

17:48.280 --> 17:49.497
Sam Landry:
So he says,

17:49.540 --> 17:52.065
"How many acres
do you own?"

17:52.110 --> 17:53.884
And he says, "Well,

17:53.940 --> 17:56.363
I own a few cows."

17:56.420 --> 18:00.026
[ conversation trails off ]

18:00.070 --> 18:03.073
If it ain't
Miss Charley Bordelon
herself.

18:03.120 --> 18:07.386
Welcome to your first meeting
of the St. Josephine
Sugarcane Society.

18:07.430 --> 18:09.557
We started
an hour ago.

18:09.610 --> 18:12.170
